Advanced hybrid manufacturing of printed electronics represents a cutting-edge approach that combines traditional printing techniques with sophisticated additive manufacturing processes. 
This integrated technologies enables complex functionalities and diverse materials into the production of electronic components. 
<br>
<br>
<b> Our current work explores:</b>
<ul>
<li> <b> Fusion of additive and hybrid manufacturing processes for printed electronics </b> </li>
<li> <b> Design and development of multifunctional conformal surfaces </b> </li>
<li> <b> Process development and optimization for scalability </b> </li>